Gideon Mendel’s images exert power through unflinching confrontation, and eerie stillness and quiet. It comes from Mendel’s practised precision and deliberate composition in ordering horror and beauty in these waterscapes where the natural order of things has been inverted. Maverick Citizen is publishing some of Mendel’s images on the day of the Global Strike. Read his interview with Ufrieda Ho here. MC  Please note you must be a Maverick Insider to comment. Sign up here or sign in if you are already an Insider.